  "doc_id": "1956",
  "text": "Compared with the wt control mice, the ear swelling response in STAT6 Ϫ/Ϫ mice significantly decreased at 24 h after the challenge. However, the reduction in ear swelling was not significant at 48 h after the challenge in the TNCB-induced CHS. The peak response of ear swelling was observed at 48 but not 24 h after challenge in STAT6 Ϫ/Ϫ mice sensitized with Oxa, TNCB, or DNFB as the contact allergen. These data may be consistent with the recent demonstration that IL-4 plays a major role in the initiation phase of CHS and inhibits the late phase of CHS [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, our results do not correlate with those of CHS in IL-4 Ϫ/Ϫ mice, as the Oxa-induced CHS did not diminish in the IL-4 Ϫ/Ϫ mice [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . It is well known that the Th2 response was completely diminished in STAT6 Ϫ/Ϫ mice, but a residual Th2 response has been clearly observed in IL-4 Ϫ/Ϫ mice [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . This may explain the marked differences of CHS in response to a hapten challenge between the IL-4 Ϫ/Ϫ mice and STAT6 Ϫ/Ϫ mice.",
